details.value:
Qualifications:

Enrolled a Bachelor's degree in Engineering, Mathematics, Computer Science or other relevant field focusing on information security.

A keen interest in information security and a desire to learn more on how we need to build systems that can be trusted.

Preferred Qualifications:

The qualifications below are a big plus, however, are not required

Experience working with information or human security concepts including tools such as Metasploit, Kali Linux, Snort, Wireshark;

Experience in application, user, network, mobile or cloud security;

Experience with social media security concepts;

Secure software development standards;

Experience with scripting languages in Linux and/or Windows environments;

Experience with cloud or distributed networking environments;

Java, C/C++, Python, Ruby, and/or SQL Language(s); and

Virtualization Technologies.

Comments/Special Considerations:

To be qualified you must be able to obtain and hold security clearance at a Reliability Status level and pass a security assessment for the Controlled Goods Program.

MDA is an equal opportunity employer prizing diversity and inclusion. We are committed to treating all employees and applicants for employment with respect and dignity. If you require assistance and/or reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please feel free to notify us.

Salary:

The compensation range for this position is $23 - $26 hourly.
